trend_summary: Imagery shows steady suburbanisation: forested blocks give way to new housing tracts along main roads, roads widen and multiply, and a reservoir is re-engineered. Tree cover shrinks most on the northwest flank while southeast neighbourhoods infill. Built-up fabric remains discontinuous but grows enough to reach overall medium density suburban character.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of detached-housing subdivisions in the southeastern quadrant.
Large-scale tree clearance and browning on the northwest side, reducing canopy cover.
Upgrade and widening of the principal east-west highway and connecting arterials.
Creation or enlargement of the central-eastern reservoir and surrounding embankments.
Emergence of new cul-de-sac street patterns on the southern fringe.
